	)
	(text_box "About:\n- TPS1200 is main battery switch. It controller power FETs and protect against battery overvoltage, undervoltage and overcurrent\n\nDesign Parameters:\n- 7-cell battery, minimum cut-off voltage 2.5V x 7 = 17.5V (set by EN/UVLO and OV resistors)\n- 7 cell battery, maximum cut-off voltage 4.3V x 7 = 30.1V (set by EN/UVLO and OV resistors)\n- Maximum battery cut-off current = 20A (set by shunt resistor and ISCP resistor)\n- Burn-out fuse will blow at 25A within 0.3~0.6S\n\nHow to use it:\n1) Set DRV_MAIN_EN to 1 to enable TPS1200\n2) Set DRV_PRE_FET_EN to 1 to start precharge/predischarge (optional)\n3) Set DRV_FET_EN to 1 to enable main FETs. This enables battery charge/discharge\n4) Watch for DRV_FLT_GD. When 1, FET gate voltage is good\n5) Watch for ~{FLT}. When 0, there is a fault present (overvoltage, undervoltage, excesive current..)\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 17.78 20.32 0)
